What is Git?
-------------
-Git is distributed version control system(VCS) used to track code changes,
-Collaborate with teams, and manage software versions
-As a DevOps Engineer, Git is the first and most essential skill becuase every CI/CD pipeline starts from Git.
-CI-Contineous Integretion/CD-Contineous delivery or deployment

Why Git is important in DevOps?
-------------------------------
-Store code versions safely
-Collaboration with developers
-Integrates with Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab, etc
-Supports automation and code review
-Used for IaC(infrastrucuture as Code)

Core Git Concepts:
------------------
Concept					Meaning
-------------------------------
Respository				Project folder controlled by git
Local repo				On your system
Remote repo				On Github
Branch					Paralled development line
Merge					Combine changes from 1 branch to another branch
Pull Request(PR)/
merge request			Request merge code into main branch (ex: main branch and shiva branch)


